transform = transforms.Compose([transforms.Resize((224, 224)),
                                transforms.ToTensor(),
                                transforms.Normalize((0.5, 0.5, 0.5), (0.5, 0.5, 0.5))])

dataset = datasets.ImageFolder(root = f"{path}/Garbage classification/Garbage classification", transform = transform)
train_set, valid_set, test_set = torch.utils.data.random_split(dataset, [0.7, 0.15, 0.15])

train_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(train_set, batch_size = batch_size, shuffle = True)
valid_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(valid_set, batch_size = batch_size, shuffle = False)

def draw_samples(loader, size = 5):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(size, size, figsize=(10,10))
    indexes = np.random.randint(low=0, high=len(loader.dataset), size=size*size)
    fig.suptitle("Garbage classification samples")
    for i in range(size):
        for j in range(size):
            idx = indexes[i * size + j]

            image, label = loader.dataset[idx]
            image = image.permute(1, 2, 0)
            image = image * torch.tensor([0.5, 0.5, 0.5]) + torch.tensor([0.5, 0.5, 0.5])
            image = image.clip(0, 1)

            axs[i, j].imshow(image)
            axs[i, j].axis('off')
            axs[i, j].set_title(f"{loader.dataset.dataset.classes[label]}")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

draw_samples(train_loader)

ResNet-50



















In [34]:



     


def resnet_50(num_classes, is_modified = False):
    model = models.resnet50(weights = models.ResNet50_Weights.DEFAULT)
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False
    layer = model.fc.in_features
    if is_modified:
      model.fc = nn.Sequential(nn.Dropout(0.2),
                               nn.Linear(layer, layer // 2),
                               nn.ReLU(),
                               nn.Linear(layer // 2, num_classes))
    else:
        model.fc = nn.Linear(layer, num_classes)

    return model



     























VIT-B-16



















In [35]:



     


def vit_b_16(num_classes, is_modified = False):
    model = models.vit_b_16(weights = models.ViT_B_16_Weights.DEFAULT)
    for params in model.parameters():
        params.requires_grad = False
    layer = model.heads[0].in_features
    if is_modified:
        model.heads = nn.Sequential(nn.Dropout(0.2),
                                    nn.Linear(layer, layer // 2),
                                    nn.ReLU(),
                                    nn.Linear(layer // 2, num_classes))
    else:
        model.heads = nn.Linear(layer, num_classes)
    return model



     























MobileNet-V2



















In [36]:



     


def mobilenet_v2(num_classes, is_modified = False):
    model = models.mobilenet_v2(weights = models.MobileNet_V2_Weights.DEFAULT)
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False
    layer = model.classifier[1].in_features
    if is_modified:
        model.classifier[1] = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(0.2),
            nn.Linear(layer, layer // 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(layer // 2, num_classes))
    else:
        model.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(layer, num_classes)

    return model



     























Shufflenet-v2-x2-0



















In [37]:



     


def shufflenet_v2_x2_0(num_classes, is_modified = False):
    model = models.shufflenet_v2_x2_0(weights = models.ShuffleNet_V2_X2_0_Weights.DEFAULT)
    for params in model.parameters():
        params.requires_grad = False
    layer = model.fc.in_features
    if is_modified:
        model.fc = torch.nn.Sequential(nn.Dropout(0.2),
                                       nn.Linear(layer, layer // 2),
                                       nn.ReLU(),
                                       nn.Linear(layer // 2, num_classes))
    else:
      model.fc = torch.nn.Linear(layer, num_classes)
    return model

In [13]:



     


device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu")
cross_entropy_loss = nn.CrossEntropyLoss().to(device)
print(device)



     




















    
    






cuda
























In [14]:



     


def train(model, optimizer):
    model.train()
    train_loss = []
    train_accuracy = []

    start = time.time()
    for data in train_loader:
        images = data[0].to(device)
        labels = data[1].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        outputs = model(images)

        loss = cross_entropy_loss(outputs, labels)
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

        train_loss.append(loss)
        train_accuracy.append(torch.mean(torch.argmax(outputs, dim = 1) == labels, dtype = float))

    train_time = time.time() - start
    return train_loss, train_accuracy, train_time

def valid(model):
    model.eval()
    valid_loss = []
    valid_accuracy = []
    valid_f1_score = []

    start = time.time()
    with torch.no_grad():
        for data in valid_loader:
            images = data[0].to(device)
            labels = data[1].to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            loss = cross_entropy_loss(outputs, labels)

            valid_loss.append(loss)
            valid_accuracy.append(torch.mean(torch.argmax(outputs, dim = 1) == labels, dtype = float))
            valid_f1_score.append(torch.tensor(f1_score(torch.argmax(outputs, dim = 1).cpu(), labels.cpu(), average = 'macro')))

    valid_time = time.time() - start
    return valid_loss, valid_accuracy, valid_time, valid_f1_score

def test(model):
    test_f1_score = []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for data in test_loader:
            images = data[0].to(device)
            labels = data[1].to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            test_f1_score.append(torch.tensor(f1_score(torch.argmax(outputs, dim = 1).cpu(), labels.cpu(), average = 'macro')))
    return test_f1_score



     



















In [18]:



     


def experiment(model):
    f1_valid = []
    optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr = learning_rate)
    for epoch in range(epochs):
        print(f'epoch: {epoch}\n')
        train_loss, train_accuracy, train_time = train(model, optimizer)
        print(f"train loss= {torch.stack(train_loss).mean():.3f}, "
              f"train accuracy= {torch.stack(train_accuracy).mean():.3f}, " +
              f"train time= {train_time:.3f}")
        valid_loss, valid_accuracy, valid_time, valid_f1_score = valid(model)
        print(f"valid loss= {torch.stack(valid_loss).mean():.3f}, " +
              f"valid accuracy= {torch.stack(valid_accuracy).mean():.3f}, " +
              f"valid time= {valid_time:.3f}, " +
              f"valid f1-score= {torch.stack(valid_f1_score).mean():.3f} \n")
        f1_valid.append(torch.stack(valid_f1_score).mean())

    test_f1_score = test(model)
    print(f"test f1-score:{torch.stack(test_f1_score).mean():.3f} ")
    return f1_valid, torch.stack(test_f1_score).mean()

num_classes = 6
def experiment_resnet_50(is_modified = False):
    model = resnet_50(num_classes, is_modified).to(device)
    return experiment(model)


def experiment_vit_b_16(is_modified = False):
    model = vit_b_16(num_classes, is_modified).to(device)
    return experiment(model)


def experiment_mobilenet_v2(is_modified = False):
    model = mobilenet_v2(num_classes, is_modified).to(device)
    return experiment(model)

def experiment_shufflenet_v2_x2_0(is_modified = False):
    model = shufflenet_v2_x2_0(num_classes, is_modified).to(device)
    return experiment(model)

def draw_f1_score(f1_score, model_name):
    x = range(epochs)
    plt.title(f"{model_name}")
    plt.plot(x, f1_score, marker="o")
    plt.xlabel("epoch")
    plt.ylabel("f1-score")
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()
